It’s the end of Endometriosis awareness month, but the awareness doesn’t stop.

-On February 12th, 2018 I was officially diagnosed. On February 14th, 2023 I gave birth to my beautiful baby boy 💛

-I don’t take these small moments for granted because I didn’t think this would be my experience. I’m so glad God had other plans for me.
Unfortunately, for so many women, this isn’t their reality as of yet. It breaks my heart each and every day. But, this is why I do what I do. This is why I shed light on this chronic illness. So those women too can have answers and do the work necessary to bare their miracle baby. We must continue spreading awareness because maybe young girls can get diagnosed a lot sooner. 7-12 years is unacceptable! 
We need more specialist, more voices, more HELP! 

- thank you @doonausa for using your platform to spread the word and interviewing me! If you guys haven’t checked it out yet, head to their instagram! 
#endometriosis #endometriosisawareness #doona

@kimberlycherrell I’ve been ✨influenced✨ and you were so right about these

-Gel X nails have been saving life because I personally don’t have time to go to the salon anymore and press-on’s don’t last as much as I would like. But one thing about it, I ways dread the painting part. Especially because I can’t do no French tips 😂

So, when Kim put us on to these already painted Gel X tips from @amazon I had to hand my card over! This is going to be a life saver!

- STEPS
1. Clean those cuticles
2. Measure each nail for the perfect size
3. Apply your mail dehydrator and follow up with the nail primer 
4. Apply a small amount of nail glue to your natural nail and cure for 10 seconds 
5. Apply the glue to the tip and gently place the nail on starting at a 90° angle!
6. Cure for 30 seconds
7. Repeat each step until complete
8. Add some cuticle oil and you’re done 💅🏽

#gelx #gelxnails #frenchtipnails

In honor of stinky booty turning two months today, let’s talk about the first time Allen had a blow out and I thought I was going to ☠️

Allen was sound asleep in his bassinet. Life was great. I woke up at like 3:45 per usual and he was making the softest baby grunts which he usually does when he’s hungry so I say to myself “it’s feeding time. Let me make my baby his bottle”
And then I hear four very wet farts so I’m like ohhhh he’s pooping let me give him a minute. 10 minutes go by and I’m like ok he should be done. He had fell back asleep.

I pick him up and I feel he’s wet but I thought he peed through his clothes. It was dark and I couldn’t see what was waiting for him. So I took him to his room and when I cut that light on I almost died.

I was in a full blown panicking because it was on his hands and he sucks on his finger so I was just like omggg please don’t taste your poop 🤢 

I woke Dominique up because this was definitely a two person a job. So picture us, two first time parents who had never experienced such a thing, running around not knowing our next move.
I wore two mask because the smell was TERRIBLE! How could so much come out of one little human?!

We decided a bath was the best option. We both bathed him and tossed out everything the poop touched. The end.

HAPPY TWO MONTHS STINKY BOOTY BUTT 😘

#babyblowout #firsttimeparents

I’ll be the first to admit, I didn’t understand the purpose of paying attention to wake windows. I use to take so much pride in saying “I’m just going with the flow and following sleepy cues”

While there’s absolutely NOTHING wrong with that, here’s why I encourage you to follow wake windows 

✨It Takes Out The Guessing✨
If you know your child can only be awake for two hours max without getting cranky, you know at that two hour mark EXACTLY why your child might be moody. It’s not their diaper, it’s not because they want to be picked up, they’re tired.

✨You Can Plan Your Day Better✨
Knowing exactly what time Allen will be napping has allowed me to schedule what time to cook, clean, shower, have a meeting, literally whatever! 

✨Helps With Sleeping Through The Night✨
Before I started paying attention to his wake windows, I didn’t understand why he wasn’t sleeping much at night. Once I put a little more focus on it I realized his wake windows was too short for his age! Then, I actively worked on extending them. Besides the growth spurts and regressions, his sleep has improved drastically!

Hope this helps!!
#wakewindows #newparentslife #motherhood

✨Use Products Curated For Your Hair Needs✨
Not all products are created equal. Some may have a thicker consistency, some may be geared towards protein sensitive hair, I mean the list goes on. Figure out your hair needs and move accordingly 

✨Get Your Seasonal Trims✨
Wash day can be an absolute nightmare if you’re dealing with single strand knots. It can cause breakage and a longer detangling session. Get that trim sis. 

✨WATER WATER WATER✨
If your hair is still feeling dry after wash day, that’s because you’re not implementing enough water. Water is the ultimate hydrator for your hair. While applying your products, make sure you are also adding water. 

✨Fogless Mirror✨
If you’re not using a fogless mirror in your shower while doing your hair, how are you even seeing anything? 😂 this allows you to be sure that you’ve gotten all of the conditioner and shampoo out
